So, my thinking was that 13 is a number that only really works with Wolves and Vamps, but if you're going to do Vamps, there isn't space for a second Evil team. The issue with that is that if the Vamp gets caught on N1, the game is potentially just over, or much more good-sided than anticipated, and it's not an enjoyable experience when most N1 checks are random. So I put in two stalkers (I don't have an inebriated aura, which is why one was aura afflicted and the other was just drunk) with differing afflictions, but weakened them both to ensure that the game wasn't just over on D2. I wanted a sub-faction in for potential basement sussiness, and put in the Illu because I wanted them to think that maybe there were hidden masons, rather than them being the only sub-faction. The problem with having a sub-faction in a game is you can potentially hard clear three villagers through it, so that was why the game was relatively light in other living intel gatherers. Sadly, my illu leader got fammed N1 and my stalkers found themselves under hella suspicion and the village was always going to struggle to recover from that. I put in VM fam roles for the village side, to both hint towards Vamps and misdirect about what Vamp it was. The meta is very much tilted towards VC at the moment, and that's fine, but I thought it might give some pause into whether there actually was a VM. The Villagers with items were intended to replicate other Fammy roles, so Vanilla with manacles is effectively a court who can see blocks, GY records makes you GDish. I considered giving a harlot rune as well and make that villager clumsy so they couldn't use it N1, but decided against. The tenacity ring, bear trap and dagger were all intended as things to be passed to intel roles (or used on them in the case of the bear trap), which wouldn't particularly affect the Vamp, but would impact on their fams to some degree. I had something else instead of the bear trap and switched it at the last minute, but can't remember what it was now. Might have been the orb. Whatever it was, I decided it was going to impact things too much. It's always tough to see something you carefully consider get blown up by the N1 recruit on the most powerful role the village has, and if it was possible to give someone a one night Tough, like with weakened, I'd have done that to the Illu Leader. I even thought about messaging Kirsch and asking if he would be happy to take a protection item off the illu leader after N1. But didn't and thought that was probably more mod interference than would be reasonable. I'd have mentioned it in the mod text if that was the case, but it's a bit too much. I stand by 0.25 ferrets, the setup is fairly standard, with a little bit of spice. Maybe I shouldn't have drunked/concussed the Stalkers, I can see that with the N1 weakened being fair, I was just overly worried about 3 members of the Illu being proven lit on top additional stalker intel. I enjoyed watching the game, thanks very much for playing!.
